A man was rushed to hospital today after being stabbed at a bus stop. The victim, who is in his 30s, suffered severe hand wounds and remains in hospital after the attack in Carshalton, south London. Emergency services were called to the bus stop at 10.03am but the man had already left the scene on a bus prior to the arrival of police. At 10.09am, Metropolitan Police were called to reports of a man aboard a Route 151 at Wrythe Lane in Carshalton with a knife injury to the hand. Officers believe this was the same injured man from the first call. Crime scenes are in place at both locations, My London reports. The injured man was taken to a West London hospital. No update has been given on the condition of the man. Anyone with information who has not yet spoken with police should call 101 or Tweet @MetCC quoting 2100/07Feb. To remain 100% anonymous call the independent charity Crimestoppers on 0800 555 111 or visit crimestoppers-uk.org.  We'll be bringing you the very latest updates, pictures and video on this breaking news story. Please check back regularly for updates on this developing story . Get email updates on the day’s biggest stories straight to your inbox by signing up for our newsletters . Get all the big headlines, pictures, analysis, opinion and video on the stories that matter to you by following Express every time you see our name. Follow Express on Google News. Follow Express on Apple News. Follow Express on Flipboard. You can follow us and sign up for Twitter alerts here @daily_express. Keep up-to-date with your must-see news, features, videos and pictures throughout the day by following us on Facebook at Daily Express.  